HEADWORD: Decantation
<hw>De`can*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>d⟦eacute⟧cantation</ets>.]</ety> <def>The act of pouring off a
clear liquor gently from its lees or sediment, or from one vessel into
another.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

